From 3 until 4 June Rand Water is planning shutdowns in parts of Johannesburg. For more, eNCA speaks to From the 3rd to the 4th of June Rand Water is planning shutdowns in parts of Johannesburg. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Rand Water is planning shutdowns in parts of Johannesburg from 3 to 4 June. This is to cross-connect the newly constructed pipeline to the existing pipeline at Randjesfontein. READ: Slight decline in SA’s water levels "The areas that will be affected in the City of Johannesburg will be the western parts of Joburg, the Randburg area, the Roodepoort area, and certain areas within Soweto," said Johannesburg Water Operations General Manager Etienne Hugo. Watch the video above for more details on this story.